spec: mp3241
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(multiprocessing)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html"
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.managers.html"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source code"
    - "any proprietary source"
  notes:
    - "Wave 663 (mp3241): __rtruediv__, __rfloordiv__, __rmod__ dict-presence (reflected division/modulo) for multiprocessing types."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
    - "Classes covered: multiprocessing.Process, pool.Pool, pool.AsyncResult, pool.MapResult, managers.SyncManager, managers.BaseListProxy, managers._BaseDictProxy, managers._BaseSetProxy."
    - "Key finding (__rtruediv__): all 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __rtruediv__. multiprocessing.Process manages a subprocess lifecycle (start/join/terminate/kill); reflected true division is undefined for process objects. pool.Pool dispatches work to worker processes; n / pool is not a defined Python expression. pool.AsyncResult and pool.MapResult are result handles; reflected division is absent. managers.BaseListProxy proxies list — list does NOT define __rtruediv__ (list has no true division data model from either side). managers._BaseDictProxy proxies dict — dict defines neither __truediv__ nor __rtruediv__. managers._BaseSetProxy proxies set — set does not support true division of any kind. managers.SyncManager: server process hosting shared objects; no division protocol defined."
    - "Key finding (__rfloordiv__): all 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __rfloordiv__. Reflected floor division is the mirror of __floordiv__. multiprocessing types define no __floordiv__ (confirmed false in wave 659), so __rfloordiv__ is also absent. Process/Pool/AsyncResult/MapResult are process-management and result-handle types. managers.BaseListProxy proxies list — list defines no __floordiv__ or __rfloordiv__. managers._BaseDictProxy proxies dict — dict defines no arithmetic operators. managers._BaseSetProxy proxies set — set defines no floor division from either side. managers.SyncManager: no arithmetic protocol defined."
    - "Key finding (__rmod__): all 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __rmod__. Reflected modulo (__rmod__) is invoked when n % obj is attempted. multiprocessing types define no __mod__ (confirmed false in wave 659), so __rmod__ is equally absent. Critical note on managers.BaseListProxy and managers._BaseDictProxy: neither list nor dict defines __rmod__. managers._BaseSetProxy proxies set — set defines no modulo operator from either side. managers.SyncManager, Process, Pool, AsyncResult, MapResult: none implement a modulo or format-string interface. None of the 8 subjects expose the % operator from either side."
    - "Proxy class note — BaseListProxy: wave 658 found BaseListProxy.__add__ = true and BaseListProxy.__mul__ = true (forwarding list's + and * operators). Wave 662 confirmed BaseListProxy.__radd__ = false and BaseListProxy.__rmul__ = false (list has no __radd__ or __rmul__). This wave confirms BaseListProxy.__rtruediv__ = false, __rfloordiv__ = false, __rmod__ = false (list has none of these reflected division/modulo operators)."
    - "All 24 values in this wave are false. multiprocessing is a process-based concurrency library; its entire API is expressed through explicit method calls, subprocess lifecycle management, and IPC — never through Python's reflected division or modulo operators."
    - "Cross-wave summary for mp subjects:"
    - "  Wave 658 (mp3166): __add__/__sub__/__mul__ — BaseListProxy __add__=true, __mul__=true; others false."
    - "  Wave 659 (mp3181): __truediv__/__floordiv__/__mod__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 660 (mp3196): __pow__/__lshift__/__rshift__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 661 (mp3211): __and__/__or__/__xor__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 662 (mp3226): __radd__/__rsub__/__rmul__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 663 (mp3241): __rtruediv__/__rfloordiv__/__rmod__ — all false for all 8."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __rtruediv__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__rtruediv__')
#
# All 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __rtruediv__.
# Process/Pool/AsyncResult/MapResult: process-management and result-handle
#   types; reflected true division is not defined for any of them.
# managers.BaseListProxy: proxies list — list does NOT define __rtruediv__.
#   Python's list has no true-division data model from either side; n / list
#   triggers int's __truediv__ which rejects list, and list has no __rtruediv__
#   fallback. Therefore BaseListProxy has no __rtruediv__.
# managers._BaseDictProxy: proxies dict — dict defines no __truediv__ or
#   __rtruediv__.
# managers._BaseSetProxy: proxies set — set does not support true division
#   from either side.
# managers.SyncManager: server process; no arithmetic protocol defined.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table mp3241.rtruediv:
  description: "multiprocessing types __rtruediv__ dict-presence checks; wave 663"
  kind: python_call_eq
  version: ">=3.9"
  error_model: python_exceptions
  category: dict_contains
  id_prefix: mp3241

  columns: [id, function, args, expected]
  rows:
